30-Second Interview Answer

std::shared_ptr is a C++11 smart pointer that enables multiple smart pointers to 
share ownership of the same object. It maintains a reference count in a control block. 
Every copy increments the count, and every destruction or reset decrements it. 
When the reference count reaches zero, the object is automatically deleted. 
It is commonly used when multiple objects need shared ownership, while weak_ptr is used to avoid circular references.

